						               													<description>Corporate Life is a worker placement and area control game with special actions. Each turn players choose an ACE card from a hand of 3 and then select 1 of 3 possible actions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A: Authorized Action - to place or move workers within the organization. &amp;#10;C: Claim Credit - to score points with the board on your journey to CEO. &amp;#10;E: Executive Event - Seize opportunities created by well meaning, but ill-advised executives.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Positioning Cubers into key organizational positions grants a player access to department bonuses. Some departments protect your Cubers from actions and events, some augment Claiming Credit, and others alter a player's hand. Leveraging these department actions is key to getting ahead of your competition!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play continues until one player gains access to the CEO's office (25+ Promotion Points). All players take an even number of turns and the player with the most promotion points is appointed the new CEO and wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is not a business simulation! It is a lighthearted poke at office politics, bizarre corporate structures, and the underhanded action of those that subscribe to the lifestyle of Corporate Life.&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Welcome to Corporate Life&amp;hellip;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You&amp;rsquo;ve always known you should be in charge. When it comes to directing others, Hollywood&amp;rsquo;s titans would be wise to seek your advice. That&amp;rsquo;s why you joined the Inc.Co LLC team - to seize the CEO reins. Unfortunately, your understanding of how it&amp;rsquo;s supposed to be and that of the Board of Directors is a wee bit out of alignment. Somehow, you&amp;rsquo;ve landed in a mailroom job. But things are about to change. All you need is the right Cubers (Cubical Workers) in the right position and the company will be yours!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;'Corporate Life is a game of competitive manipulation and control. Players vie to maneuver Cubers into key department positions, seize credit for the work of others, and pursuit of that coveted CEO promotion.&amp;#10;- from back of box&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
